1-2 are things I usually have memmed like summon orb or are there for quick access/regularity of use like summon companion, gate, invis, all self-buffs...<br>
3-4 debuffs, common summons like muzzle, ring of flight CotH, modrod, pet heal<br>
5-6 are all my nukes/dmg shields/ae's + burst of flame <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Next 6 are uncommon spells like gift of xev, coldstone that I usually only cast when I login, high level pets for specific encounters + 49 fire, valiant companion, bind, etc. and all other spells that I might use but don't want to file away in the back of the book (bristlebane's bundle, banishment, etc.).<br>
<br>
Then there's a few blank pages (kept open for spells I don't have yet, plus it serves to divide the front/back of my book nicely) , then all the outdated spells like the old self AC buffs, nukes, summons, and pets categorized by type/spell level per page. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/useth1452.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Seth1452</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(3/11/02 8:19:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthelibrary.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Spell book layouts</span><hr size=1> It's interesting the variety in how mages order their spells.<br>
<br>
Some put pets first, then pet buffs, then item summons for pet, then dmg spells and DS and such... They feel that the pet is the most important thing and deserves the #1 speed dial button.<br>
<br>
Others put dmg spells first, then pets on page 2, continuing with pet buffs, then DS and other utility spells like malise or whatever, then item summons. These people feel that the mage's power is truely a blend of all the mage's capabilities and hold no value to any over others.<br>
<br>
Then there are those that put all their damage spells like nukes and AoEs and DS first, then pets and pet buffs, then either item summons or utility spells. These mages are thinking they use nukes and DS more often and that comes first.. pet only gets summoned occasionaly and buffs, etc. Then utility spells/item summons that are only used once or twice while playing in one zone or have uses limited to certain situations (malosi).  They are thinking sure, pet does more dmg than them and stuff but once it's there they're a nuker/support and that's what they do durring the fight. Those should come first.<br>
<br>
There's some mage psychology for ya. Then again I'm tired as heck. It was me bed time yesterday.  Just pokin' at yer brains.  I'll send my own arrangement soon.<br>
<br>
Valmeria Nightblaze<br>
Vending Machine Extraordinare<br>
Part-time 54th Elementalist<br>
Quellious Server<br>
